The '''''Bahman-nama''''' ({{lang-fa|بهمن نامه}}) is a [[Persian language|Persian]] [[Epic poetry|epic]] poem of 9500 [[Distich]]s (couplets)<ref name="Iranica">[http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/bahman-nama-epic-poem  W. L. Hanaway, Jr., "BAHMAN-NĀMA" in Encyclopaedia Iranica]</ref> about [[Kay Bahman|Bahman]], the son of [[Esfandiyar]] of the royal [[Kayanid]] dynasty. The earliest attestation of this work is in the book [[Mojmal al-tawarikh]], which gives the author as [[Irānshāh (poet)|Īrānšāh b. Abi'l Khayr]].<ref>The manuscript reads Iranshan however Bahar believes that this is scribal error and it should be Iranshah.  Most scholars have followed his convention</ref>

