'''Lilia Stepanova''' (born 29 July 1987) is a [[contortionist]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Oameni...de cauciuc |url=http://www.jurnalul.ro/fun/fun/oameni-de-cauciuc-573841.html |work=[[Jurnalul Naţional]] |language=Romanian |date=3 April 2011 |accessdate=10 June 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Iată-i pe cei mai tari contorsionişti din lume! |url=http://www.libertatea.ro/detalii/articol/contorsionisti-tari-lume-331189.html |work=[[Libertatea]] |language=Romanian |date=16 April 2011 |accessdate=10 June 2011 }}</ref> She was born in [[Chişinău]], [[Moldova]], to parents who were also contortionists. She started training with her mother at the age of five.

{{As of|2010}}, Stepanova is living in [[Las Vegas, Nevada]], where she is known for performing at many [[NBA]] halftime shows.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hruby|first=Patrick|title=Seven minutes of wow|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/espn/eticket/story?page=110604/NBAhalftime|work=Outside the Lines|publisher=ESPN|accessdate=3 July 2011}}</ref> She is also known for her ability to perform [[archery]] with her feet while on hand-balancing canes, the piece she performed on Season 1 of ''[[America's Got Talent (season 1)|America's Got Talent]]''.

==Performances==
She has appeared as a guest artist on shows including:
*"[[The View (U.S. TV series)|The View]]";
*"[[America's Got Talent]]";
*"[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]";
*"[[Steve Harvey's Big Time]]";
*"[[Best Damn Sports Show Period]]"; and
*"[[E:60]]".

She has also been in a commercial for [[Nykredit]], a [[Denmark|Danish]] bank.

